<i>♫ Everything acts so unknown ♫</i>

159
00:19:32,837 --> 00:19:36,553
<i>♫ I just need someone to hold on ♫</i>

160
00:19:38,003 --> 00:19:40,587
<i>♫ How to get out of the black hole ♫</i>

161
00:19:40,587 --> 00:19:44,003
<i>♫ Every day is... ♫</i>

162
00:19:44,003 --> 00:19:46,012
Sorry, we'll start over.

163
00:19:47,503 --> 00:19:49,553
Go take a break.

164
00:19:51,072 --> 00:19:53,831
Can't you feel that you're distracted?

165
00:20:03,587 --> 00:20:05,503
- Go home.
- But I...

166
00:20:05,503 --> 00:20:07,345
Go home.

167
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,553
Here's the new schedule.

168
00:20:21,253 --> 00:20:23,387
Sea, are you leaving now?

169
00:20:35,503 --> 00:20:39,637
No. Sea is not feeling well.

170
00:20:41,670 --> 00:20:43,262
I see.

171
00:20:48,212 --> 00:20:50,345
Cheng is taking away our funding.

172
00:20:54,003 --> 00:20:55,803
Why's that?

173
00:20:56,837 --> 00:20:59,378
He doesn't feel like supporting this concert.

174
00:20:59,378 --> 00:21:02,970
But don't you worry,
I'll figure something out.

175
00:21:08,378 --> 00:21:11,845
Is Sea alright?

176
00:21:14,503 --> 00:21:16,553
He doesn't seem to be.

177
00:21:21,712 --> 00:21:24,428
I may have put too much pressure on him.

178
00:21:26,255 --> 00:21:27,972
What does that mean?

179
00:21:33,003 --> 00:21:38,878
I... I told Sea that
he's the only one who can help you,

180
00:21:38,878 --> 00:21:41,637
and I also told him about the lack of funding.

181
00:21:47,128 --> 00:21:49,345
Why did you tell him that?

182
00:21:49,962 --> 00:21:52,137
Is that something he has to worry about?

183
00:21:55,087 --> 00:21:57,212
Sorry.

184
00:21:57,212 --> 00:21:59,028
Sometimes, I just forget he's only 20.

185
00:21:59,028 --> 00:22:01,412
This has nothing to do with age.

186
00:22:02,479 --> 00:22:07,845
Whether we're successful or not,
that's my own issue.

187
00:22:43,212 --> 00:22:45,803
<i>I always talk about being responsible
for myself,</i>

188
00:22:46,462 --> 00:22:51,137
<i>but... I always make it a habit to rely others.</i>

189
00:22:56,170 --> 00:23:01,678
<i>When I'm hurt, I'll run away, I can't move on.</i>

190
00:23:03,295 --> 00:23:08,262
<i>Subconsciously,
I seem to have started to rely on you.</i>

191
00:23:11,295 --> 00:23:13,068
<i>I will keep getting stronger.</i>

192
00:23:13,068 --> 00:23:15,587
<i>You are the ocean.</i>

193
00:23:15,587 --> 00:23:17,295
For Magnet.

194
00:23:17,295 --> 00:23:19,595
<i>You've caught me.</i>

195
00:23:20,795 --> 00:23:25,262
<i>I'm the one who needs you, to push me forward.</i>

196
00:23:34,003 --> 00:23:35,678
Hello?

197
00:23:40,503 --> 00:23:42,512
Well...

198
00:23:43,462 --> 00:23:45,803
Can you come over to my place?

199
00:23:52,670 --> 00:23:54,095
Hi.

200
00:23:56,587 --> 00:23:58,637
Come on in.

201
00:24:02,868 --> 00:24:04,512
Take a seat.

202
00:24:51,747 --> 00:24:53,600
Sea, I like you.
<i>[Next Episode]</i>

203
00:24:53,600 --> 00:24:56,503
One of your friends
made a romantic confession the other day.

204
00:24:56,503 --> 00:25:00,512
That friend... was you.

205
00:25:01,876 --> 00:25:05,762
From making music to falling in love.

206
00:25:06,420 --> 00:25:09,128
I want to tell you, that it was all because
I met you,

207
00:25:09,128 --> 00:25:11,470
I was able to get back on that stage again.
